name: Venus
description:
Inspired by the world renown statue "Venus de milo" 
believed to depict Aphrodite, the Greek goddess of love and beauty. This piece features an actual small scale charm of the famous statue in gold rather than marble. The Gold statue is accompanied by gold stars and a gold Bead. The main beads are constructed of Black Onyx to ensure longevity of this piece as the Venus de milo has lasted so shall this piece.

name: Enraged Pegasus
description:
Pegasus is one of the best known mythological creatures in Greek mythology. He is a winged divine stallion usually depicted as pure white in color. He was sired by Poseidon, in his role as horse-god, and foaled by the Gorgon Medusa. This piece represents a furious Pegasus in all his might and power composed of white speckles jade and crackled red jade, gold spacers and a gold feather charm for accent. 

Do Not Anger The Gods.
